$interpreted: Alliance Soldier: Hey, where're you running off to!?
Alliance Soldier: Don't forget you're a prisoner. If it weren't for the arbiter you'd still be in your cell right now! Quit screwing around!
Hestia: Hmph... Say it, don't spray it...
Puggi: Oh Hesty, Hesty~! Just look at all these people here for the tournament!
Puggi: Is everyone really so bored that they'd get all jazzed up just to stuff themselves inside some smelly arena?
Hestia: I can't believe we've been caught, and now Pang's got to join this weird tournament... We need to find a way to escape.
Puggi: Huh? Why?
Hestia: Eh? What do you mean, "why"?
Puggi: If Pang wins, then he'll be arbiter and we'll be in the clear! Tell me that wouldn't be wicked cool!
Hestia: Cool?
Puggi: "Hey, don't you know who I am!? The arbiter's my lil' bro! Now, bow before me!!"
Puggi: Hehehe~ Gettin' all tingly just thinking about it~
Hestia: Puggi! This is serious!
Alliance Soldier: What are you two whispering about over there!?
Hestia: Excuse me? Your arbiter has allowed us to watch the tournament, so can't you just stay out of our business!?
Alliance Soldier: You kept whining that it'd be 'unfair' if you couldn't watch, that's the only reason the arbiter let you out!
Hestia: And that's the truth! If we were still in our cells, how would we know if Pang was getting fair treatment!?
Alliance Soldier: Excuse me!? The Martial Arts Tournament is the Alliance's most important event. Everything's done by the books!
Hestia: And we're supposed to take your word for it? I'd rather see it for myself.
Hestia: Right, Puggi?
Hestia: Puggi!?
Alliance Soldier: I knew you'd try and escape! Quick, get 'em!
Hestia: Oh man, If I don't find Puggi quick, who knows what kind of trouble he'll get himself into...
Chiyuki: Good morning, everyone.
Adoring Soldier: (It's Hanazono Chiyuki!)
Excited Soldier: (Such beauty! Such class! Even more incredible than her parents! No wonder she's the Alliance's sweetheart~)
Obsessed Soldier: (Oooo!! Chiyuki!! She's so pretty~!! Be still, my beating heart!!)
Organiser: Good morning Miss Chiyuki, you look radiant as always~ Haven't even put make-up on yet, have you? Quite the natural beauty.
Chiyuki: Thank you.
Chiyuki: And thank you all for coming out to help with the tournament. I trust everyone is well prepared!
Chiyuki: (Whew, no one realizes I got up super early and gave myself a facial...)
Organiser: It's our pleasure! We're all honored to be able to assist you, Miss Chiyuki!
Organiser: Now, the tournament is about to begin. Just wait here for a moment, and someone will come fetch you for make-up!
Chiyuki: (I should review everything again. Such an important event, I can't afford to make any mistakes...)
Adoring Soldier: (Incredible! Miss Chiyuki looks stunning, even when she's spacing out!)
Excited Soldier: (Oh man I feel like I might have a heart attack!!)
Obsessed Soldier: (I'd give anything just to talk to her... Huh, who's that!?)
Chiyuki Fan: ...Master Chiyuki!! Master Chiyuki!!!
Chiyuki Fan: It's really you!! Hanazono Chiyuki! Am I, like, dreaming!?
Chiyuki: You're not dreaming. I am Hanazono Chiyuki, pleased to meet you.
Chiyuki Fan: Oh, wow, your voice is so beautiful!
Chiyuki Fan: Can I... Can I have your autograph!?
Organiser: Hey, you! What the heck are you doing!? Apologize to Miss Chiyuki!
Organiser: I'm so sorry, these new kids don't understand.
Chiyuki: It's just an autograph, nothing to worry about.
Chiyuki Fan: Really!? Thank you so much, Miss Chiyuki!
Chiyuki: There you go.
Chiyuki Fan: Thank you!! I'm such a big fan of yours! I've seen every single one of your performances!
Chiyuki: Is that so~? Thank you for your support.
Chiyuki Fan: Actually, my real dream isn't to be an Alliance soldier... It's really to be a performer, just like you!
Chiyuki: It was also my dream, from a young age. Maybe we could be friends~
Chiyuki Fan: F-Friends!? No... No-No-No! I... Master Chiyuki, you're very kind, but please don't say that!
Chiyuki: Huh? What did I...?
Chiyuki Fan: I'm a commoner, I know my place...
Chiyuki Fan: You're a genius, Master Chiyuki. How could we ever be friends!? That's... I can't even fathom it...
Chiyuki Fan: I'm happy just watching you from afar...
Chiyuki: But if you like performing, we could talk...
Chiyuki Fan: Please, stop flattering me! There's... There's no one in this world good enough to be Miss Chiyuki's friend!
Chiyuki: Ah... Okay, if that's how you feel...
Chiyuki Fan: Great. Then, I need to go find a good seat before it's too late.
Chiyuki Fan: I'll be cheering you on from the stands, Miss Chiyuki!
Chiyuki: Thank you for your...
Chiyuki Fan: Goodbye, Miss Chiyuki!
Organiser: Get back here! You've still got work to do!
Organiser: Apologies... Those mega-fans get one sight of you and go completely loony.
Organiser: Miss Chiyuki? Can you hear me?
Chiyuki: ......
Chiyuki: I wish I could fly away, up high with the wind...
Chiyuki: But I'm afraid... it may be cold up there...
Chiyuki: It's lonely being famous, being a "genius"... Especially a hard-working genius...
Chiyuki: Everyone thinks everything comes so easily to me. They have no idea just how much effort it takes.
Chiyuki: Even if I am the Alliance's golden child...
Chiyuki: Who the heck is she to say I can't have friends!? I'm a person, too! I'm allowed to feel lonely!
Organiser: Uh... Miss Chiyuki?
Chiyuki: W-What?
Organiser: ...You should go to make-up. It's almost time.
Chiyuki: Yes, of course!
Chiyuki: (I can do that... Be on the stage, get the applause. That's what I'm good for.)
